{"batchSize":3,"level":"info","message":"Upsert batch:","sampleMetadata":"{\"content\":\"Las Vegas Pool Masters - Your Pool Service Provider\\nPool Maintenance Services\\n### Pool Maintenance Services\\n#### 1. How to Open a Pool\\nWinter  is  over,  and  spring  is  finally  here.  Temperatures  are  rising.  The  sun  is  shining.  A  dip  in  the\\npool sounds great! But don't jump in quite yet! \\nIf your pool has been closed all winter, you'll need to do a little prep work to get your pool ready for\\nanother season of fun. Don't worry though. \\nOpening a pool is easy with these steps:\\n- Step 1: Clean up debris and check for wear and tear.\\n- Step 2: Inventory your pool chemicals.\\n- Step 3: Remove the cover and clean it.\\n- Step 4: Inspect the pool for damage or wear.\\n- Step 5: Fill the pool to the proper water level.\\n- Step 6: Turn on the pool filter and test the water.\\n#### 2. How to Close a Pool For Winter\\nAs cold weather approaches, it's time to start winterizing your swimming pool. Here's a quick guide:\\n- Step 1: Balance your water chemistry.\\n- Step 2: Add a shock treatment.\\n- Step 3: Remove and clean pool equipment.\\nPage 101\",\"source\":\"Las_Vegas_Pool_Services.pdf\",\"documentId\":\"67528276bc88bd3f828aef99\",\"page\":101}","sampleVectorId":"2e6fc46875c9d5ee4ae49efcec714713f2a1df0d73787aa9b32fac4142eddb2a","timestamp":"2024-12-06T04:50:44.906Z"}
