{"id":"2e6fc46875c9d5ee4ae49efcec714713f2a1df0d73787aa9b32fac4142eddb2a","level":"info","matchConditions":{"hasChatbotId":false,"hasMatchingUrl":false,"hasSourceType":false},"message":"Non-matching vector metadata:","metadata":{"content":"Las Vegas Pool Masters - Your Pool Service Provider\nPool Maintenance Services\n### Pool Maintenance Services\n#### 1. How to Open a Pool\nWinter  is  over,  and  spring  is  finally  here.  Temperatures  are  rising.  The  sun  is  shining.  A  dip  in  the\npool sounds great! But don't jump in quite yet! \nIf your pool has been closed all winter, you'll need to do a little prep work to get your pool ready for\nanother season of fun. Don't worry though. \nOpening a pool is easy with these steps:\n- Step 1: Clean up debris and check for wear and tear.\n- Step 2: Inventory your pool chemicals.\n- Step 3: Remove the cover and clean it.\n- Step 4: Inspect the pool for damage or wear.\n- Step 5: Fill the pool to the proper water level.\n- Step 6: Turn on the pool filter and test the water.\n#### 2. How to Close a Pool For Winter\nAs cold weather approaches, it's time to start winterizing your swimming pool. Here's a quick guide:\n- Step 1: Balance your water chemistry.\n- Step 2: Add a shock treatment.\n- Step 3: Remove and clean pool equipment.\nPage 101","documentId":"67528464bc88bd3f828af053","page":101,"source":"Las_Vegas_Pool_Services.pdf"},"timestamp":"2024-12-06T05:41:27.895Z"}
{"id":"d83cef2205f95c30c00daec7810c6c048d73fde0707c208437fc1176952d2146","level":"info","matchConditions":{"hasChatbotId":false,"hasMatchingUrl":false,"hasSourceType":false},"message":"Non-matching vector metadata:","metadata":{"content":"Las Vegas Pool Masters - Your Pool Service Provider\n- Step 4: Lower the water level.\n- Step 5: Drain your pool pump, filters, and equipment.\n- Step 6: Add a winter cover.\n#### 3. How Do You Clear Cloudy Pool Water Fast?\n- Keep it clean: Remove debris and scrub the walls.\n- Shock your pool: Add a high dose of chlorine.\n- Use a pool clarifier to bind small particles.\n- Run the filter: Let the filter run at least 8 hours a day.\nBonus tip: If the water isn't too cloudy, use a pool flocculant to settle the debris and vacuum it out.\n--- \nPage 102","documentId":"67528464bc88bd3f828af053","page":102,"source":"Las_Vegas_Pool_Services.pdf"},"timestamp":"2024-12-06T05:41:27.896Z"}
{"id":"1ec276f3d4358de49f50b804ebf719c8f20bf7604164baa76c092d81db57d09c","level":"info","matchConditions":{"hasChatbotId":false,"hasMatchingUrl":false,"hasSourceType":false},"message":"Non-matching vector metadata:","metadata":{"content":"Las Vegas Pool Masters - Your Pool Service Provider\nContact Information\n### Contact Information\nLas Vegas Pool Masters\n- Address: 123 Poolside Blvd, Las Vegas, NV 89101\n- Email: hello@luckysevenpools.com\n- Phone: (702) 123-4567\n- Website: https://luckysevenpools.com\nFor inquiries or to schedule a service, visit our Contact Page: https://luckysevenpools.com/reach-us\nor call us directly at (702) 123-4567.\nTo       book       an       appointment,       you       can       also       use       our       Calendly       link:\nhttps://calendly.com/localleads247/30min?back=1&month=2024-09.\nWe're always ready to help with all your pool needs. Contact us today for expert advice, repairs, and\nmaintenance services.\nPage 103","documentId":"67528464bc88bd3f828af053","page":103,"source":"Las_Vegas_Pool_Services.pdf"},"timestamp":"2024-12-06T05:41:27.898Z"}
